<h2>High severity issues</h2>
<p>These issues directly prevent customers from completing a purchase.</p>

<h3>Missing Add to Cart button</h3>
<p>The Add to Cart button is not found on the page, is hidden, or is disabled. Customers cannot add the product to their cart.</p>

<h3>Add to Cart not functional</h3>
<p>The button exists but clicking it doesn't actually add the item to the cart. This is detected during deep scans through purchase flow testing.</p>

<h3>Variant selection broken</h3>
<p>Customers cannot select product options like size, color, or style. This prevents them from choosing the variant they want to buy.</p>

<h3>JavaScript errors</h3>
<p>Significant JavaScript errors are occurring on the page that affect functionality. Prowl filters out routine platform errors and only flags errors that impact the shopping experience.</p>

<h3>Missing price</h3>
<p>The product price is not visible on the page. Customers cannot see how much the product costs, which can prevent purchases.</p>

<h2>Medium severity issues</h2>
<p>These issues may not block purchases but can hurt conversions and customer confidence.</p>

<h3>Missing or broken product images</h3>
<p>One or more product images failed to load. Customers rely on images to make purchase decisions.</p>

<h3>Theme rendering errors</h3>
<p>The Shopify theme has Liquid template errors that may cause parts of the page to display incorrectly.</p>

<h2>Low severity issues</h2>

<h3>Slow page load</h3>
<p>The product page takes longer than 5 seconds to load. Slow pages increase bounce rates and reduce conversions.</p>
